5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Subsection 1 of section 54-52-05 of the North Dakota Century
7 Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
8 1. a. Every eligible participating political subdivision employee, at the time the political
9 subdivision joins the plan mustshall so state in writing if the employee concurs in
10 the plan and all future eligible employees of the participating political subdivision
11 are participating members in the plan and must be enrolled in the plan within the
12 first month of employment.
13 b. Except as otherwise provided by law, every other eligible governmental unit
14 employee of a participating governmental unit is a participating member in the
15 plan and must be enrolled in the plan within the first month of employment. An
16 employee who was not enrolled in the retirement system when eligible to
17 participate must be enrolled immediately upon notice of the employee's eligibility,
18 unless the employee waives in writing the employee's right to participate for the
19 previous time of eligibility, to avoid contributing to the fund for past service.
20 c. An employee who is eligible for normal retirement who accepts a retirement
21 benefit under this chapter and who subsequently becomes employed with a
22 participating employer other than the employer with which the employee was
23 employed with at the time the employee retired under this chapter may, before
24 being re-enrolled in the retirement plan within the first month of employment,
